cEventMgrMIB.name: cEventMgrMIB
cEventMgrMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-embedded-event-manager@cisco.com
cEventMgrMIB.description: The MIB module to describe and store events generated by the Cisco Embedded Event Manager. The Cisco Embedded Event Manager detects hardware and software faults, and other events (such as OIRs) for the system. It also enables users to configure fault recovery services for system wide components. The Embedded Event Manager also provides process reliability statistics. The Embedded Event Manager is a policy driven process through which faults in the system are reported through a defined API. The Embedded Event Manager policy engine receives notifications when faults and other events occur. Embedded Event Manager policies implement recovery based on the current state of the system and the actions specified in the policy for a given event. Recovery actions are triggered when the policy is run. Developers write and customize Embedded Event Manager policies to handle faults and events.

NotifySource.name: NotifySource
NotifySource.description: The notification source of the history entry. server - Notification was sent by the Embedded Event Manager server. policy - Notification was sent from within an Embedded Event Manager policy.

ceemEventMapTable.name: ceemEventMapTable
ceemEventMapTable.description: A table containing information about ceemEventIndex value mapping. Each conceptual row specifies a unique mapping between a ceemEventIndex value, and a Embedded Event Manager event type. Rows are added dynamically as the Embedded Event Manager server learns of new event types. This occurs when Embedded Event Manager Event Detectors register with the Embedded Event Manager server.

ceemEventMapEntry.name: ceemEventMapEntry
ceemEventMapEntry.description: A mapping between an event type and an event description.

ceemEventIndex.name: ceemEventIndex
ceemEventIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies an event. Events are not persisted across reloads.

ceemEventName.name: ceemEventName
ceemEventName.description: The name of the Embedded Event Manager event.

ceemEventDescrText.name: ceemEventDescrText
ceemEventDescrText.description: This object specifies a human-readable message describing information about the Embedded Event Manager event.

ceemHistoryMaxEventEntries.name: ceemHistoryMaxEventEntries
ceemHistoryMaxEventEntries.description: The maximum number of entries that can be held in ceemHistoryEventTable.

ceemHistoryLastEventEntry.name: ceemHistoryLastEventEntry
ceemHistoryLastEventEntry.description: Index of last entry created in ceemHistoryEventTable.

ceemHistoryEventTable.name: ceemHistoryEventTable
ceemHistoryEventTable.description: A table of Embedded Event Manager events generated by this router. Conceptual row entries are dynamically added into this table when Embedded Event Manager events occur. Entries are stored in FIFO order. When the maximum number of entries has been reached in the table, the oldest entry in the table is removed immediately. When a table is reduced to a smaller size N, the oldest entries are immediately removed from the table leaving a maximum of N entries.

ceemHistoryEventEntry.name: ceemHistoryEventEntry
ceemHistoryEventEntry.description: Information about an Embedded Event Manager event which has been generated by this router. It provides up to four event types to support complex event specifications that are triggered when multiple events are published within a certain period of time.

ceemHistoryEventIndex.name: ceemHistoryEventIndex
ceemHistoryEventIndex.description: A monotonically increasing non-zero integer uniquely identifying a generated event. When it reaches the maximum value, the agent wraps the value back to 1 and may flush all existing entries in the event table.

ceemHistoryEventType1.name: ceemHistoryEventType1
ceemHistoryEventType1.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was detected. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventTable.

ceemHistoryEventType2.name: ceemHistoryEventType2
ceemHistoryEventType2.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was detected. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventTable.

ceemHistoryEventType3.name: ceemHistoryEventType3
ceemHistoryEventType3.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was detected. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventTable.

ceemHistoryEventType4.name: ceemHistoryEventType4
ceemHistoryEventType4.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was detected. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventTable.

ceemHistoryPolicyPath.name: ceemHistoryPolicyPath
ceemHistoryPolicyPath.description: The file path on the router where the Embedded Event Manager policy that was triggered is stored. If the size of the file path string is larger than 128, the end characters will be truncated.

ceemHistoryPolicyName.name: ceemHistoryPolicyName
ceemHistoryPolicyName.description: The name of the Embedded Event Manager policy that was triggered because of an Embedded Event Manager event. The name must be a valid Embedded Event Manager policy name. It must be in the form of a valid Posix filename.

ceemHistoryPolicyExitStatus.name: ceemHistoryPolicyExitStatus
ceemHistoryPolicyExitStatus.description: The exit status of the Embedded Event Manager policy execution. This value corresponds to the Posix process exit status.

ceemHistoryPolicyIntData1.name: ceemHistoryPolicyIntData1
ceemHistoryPolicyIntData1.description: Arbitrary integer data that the Embedded Event Manager policy can use. Use of this object is optional. If unused by a policy, this object will not be instantiated for that policy.

ceemHistoryPolicyIntData2.name: ceemHistoryPolicyIntData2
ceemHistoryPolicyIntData2.description: Arbitrary integer data that the Embedded Event Manager policy can use. Use of this object is optional. If unused by a policy, this object will not be instantiated for that policy.

ceemHistoryPolicyStrData.name: ceemHistoryPolicyStrData
ceemHistoryPolicyStrData.description: Arbitrary string data the Embedded Event Manager policy can use. Use of this object is optional. If unused by a policy, this object will not be instantiated for that policy.

ceemHistoryNotifyType.name: ceemHistoryNotifyType
ceemHistoryNotifyType.description: The notification type that was sent from the Embedded Event Manager. The valid values are server or policy.

ceemHistoryEventType5.name: ceemHistoryEventType5
ceemHistoryEventType5.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was detected. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventTable.

ceemHistoryEventType6.name: ceemHistoryEventType6
ceemHistoryEventType6.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was detected. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventTable.

ceemHistoryEventType7.name: ceemHistoryEventType7
ceemHistoryEventType7.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was detected. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventTable.

ceemHistoryEventType8.name: ceemHistoryEventType8
ceemHistoryEventType8.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was detected. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventTable.

ceemRegisteredPolicyTable.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyTable
ceemRegisteredPolicyTable.description: A table of Embedded Event Manager policies registered on a system. The number of entries depends on the configuration of the system. The maximum number is implementation dependent.

ceemRegisteredPolicyEntry.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyEntry
ceemRegisteredPolicyEntry.description: An entry in the table of Embedded Event Manager policies that are registered. It provides up to four event types to support complex event specifications that are triggered when multiple events are published within a certain period of time. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ceemRegisteredPolicyIndex.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyIndex
ceemRegisteredPolicyIndex.description: A monotonically increasing non-zero integer uniquely identifying a policy registration. When it reaches the maximum value, the agent wraps the value back to 1 upon receiving the next policy registration.

ceemRegisteredPolicyName.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyName
ceemRegisteredPolicyName.description: The name of the Embedded Event Manager policy that was registered. The name must be a valid Embedded Event Manager policy name. It must be in the form of a valid Posix filename.

ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType1.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType1
ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType1.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was registered by the policy. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventMapTable.

ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType2.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType2
ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType2.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was registered by the policy. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventMapTable.

ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType3.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType3
ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType3.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was registered by the policy. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventMapTable.

ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType4.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType4
ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType4.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was registered by the policy. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventMapTable.

ceemRegisteredPolicyStatus.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyStatus
ceemRegisteredPolicyStatus.description: This status indicates whether the policy is enabled or disabled.

ceemRegisteredPolicyType.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyType
ceemRegisteredPolicyType.description: This variable indicates whether this is a user or system policy.

ceemRegisteredPolicyNotifFlag.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyNotifFlag
ceemRegisteredPolicyNotifFlag.description: This flag indicates if an SNMP notification will be sent when policy is triggered.

ceemRegisteredPolicyRegTime.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyRegTime
ceemRegisteredPolicyRegTime.description: The time the policy was registered. It is stored as a 32-bit count of seconds since 0000 UTC, 1 January, 1970.

ceemRegisteredPolicyEnabledTime.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyEnabledTime
ceemRegisteredPolicyEnabledTime.description: The time the policy was last enabled. It is stored as a 32-bit count of seconds since 0000 UTC, 1 January, 1970.

ceemRegisteredPolicyRunTime.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyRunTime
ceemRegisteredPolicyRunTime.description: The last time the policy was run. It is stored as a 32-bit count of seconds since 0000 UTC, 1 January, 1970.

ceemRegisteredPolicyRunCount.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyRunCount
ceemRegisteredPolicyRunCount.description: The number of times the policy has been run.

ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType5.name: ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType5
ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType5.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was registered by the policy. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventMapTable.

ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType6.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was registered by the policy. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventMapTable.

ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType7.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was registered by the policy. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventMapTable.

ceemRegisteredPolicyEventType8.description: The type of Embedded Event Manager event which was registered by the policy. The value corresponds to an entry in the ceemEventMapTable.

cEventMgrServerEvent.name: cEventMgrServerEvent
cEventMgrServerEvent.description: This notification is sent by the Embedded Event Manager server after it has run a policy associated with the event ceemHistoryEventType that was received.

cEventMgrPolicyEvent.name: cEventMgrPolicyEvent
cEventMgrPolicyEvent.description: This notification is configured to be sent from within an Embedded Event Manager policy after an Embedded Event Manager event ceemHistoryEventType has occurred. If one or more of the objects ceemHistoryPolicyIntData1, ceemHistoryPolicyIntData2, and ceemHistoryPolicyStrData are not instantiated, then the varbind for the object(s) not instantiated will contain the value 'noSuchInstance'.

cEventMgrDescrGroup.description: A collection of managed objects defining the description of Embedded Event Manager events.

cEventMgrNotificationsGroup.name: cEventMgrNotificationsGroup
cEventMgrNotificationsGroup.description: The collection of notifications used to indicate changes to the ceemHistoryTable.
